# Dashboard shell (must follow)

## Single source of truth
- All `/dashboard/*` paths and sidebar labels live in **`frontend/src/config/dashboard-nav.ts`** only.
- Adding a screen = add **one** `DashboardNavItem` there (path + roles + label). Paths flow into `dashboardChildPathSet` automatically — do not maintain a second list.

## Routing
- Under `/dashboard`, use **only** the existing pattern in `App.tsx`: `index` + **one** splat route → `DashboardNestedPage`.
- **Never** add per-path `<Route path="work/leads" />` (or similar) under `/dashboard` — that duplicates the shell and drifts from nav.

## Nav quality
- **No duplicate labels** visible to the same role (e.g. two “Lead pool” with same wording — disambiguate: “Admin lead pool” vs “Lead pool”).
- **No section heading** for the lone “Dashboard” link: use `label: ''` on that section (see `id: 'main'`).
- Avoid **Settings → Settings**: first item should be **“General”** (or similar), not repeating the section title.

## Placeholders
- Feature stubs use **`DashboardPlaceholderPage`** — **title only** unless the feature needs real layout. No “Shell” badges, route path echo, or long placeholder copy.
- **Exception:** **`IntelligenceWorkPage`** (`/dashboard/intelligence`) — short copy + **`useMetaQuery`**; redirect to `/dashboard` when **`features.intelligence`** is false after fetch (not placeholder data).
- **Shell stubs:** paths listed in **`frontend/src/config/shell-stub-routes.ts`** render **`ShellStubPage`** (TanStack Query → JSON stub). **`WalletPage`** / **`FinanceRechargesPage`** use **`/api/v1/wallet/*`**. **`DashboardNestedPage`** is **`lazy`** + **`Suspense`** in **`App.tsx`** for a route-level skeleton.

## Clutter
- No redundant tips, duplicate “Back” + header **Home**, or extra dev toggles in the chrome. Role preview stays **one** compact control unless product requires more.
- **`useSyncRoleFromMe`** (in `DashboardLayout`) aligns Zustand role with **`GET /api/v1/auth/me`** when `user_id` + server role change; the header select remains a **preview** until the session identity changes — do not remove that hook when editing auth.

## AI / flags
- Do not reintroduce header checkboxes for feature flags. **`useMetaQuery`** → `GET /api/v1/meta` supplies **`features.intelligence`**; pass **`ClientNavFlags`** into **`filterDashboardNav(role, flags)`** — never a lone hardcoded toggle in the shell.

## Plan checklist
- Cross-check **`docs/MYLE_VL2_CHECKLIST.md`** before closing a milestone so nav, API, and auth items stay aligned.
